  - adoption
---

The person using ChatGPT to generate a birthday card and the person using Claude with persistent context as a daily thinking partner are having completely different experiences. They're not even using the same technology in any meaningful sense. And yet the first person feels qualified to declare it a fad, because their experience tells them so.

They're not wrong about what they experienced. They're wrong about what's possible. That's a distinction worth being precise about.

The sceptics are right that a lot of what passes for AI usage today is shallow and overhyped. They're just wrong about what that means. It doesn't mean AI is a bubble. It means most people haven't figured out how to use it yet. That's a very different problem.
